 Adamawa State Governor Ahmadu Fintiri has approved the appointment of a new chairman for the Adamawa State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board. The new man at the helm of the Muslim Pilgrims Board is Sheikh Ibrahim Daware. Daware, a foremost Islamic scholar and cleric, is also currently the national chairman of Zawiatu Darikatu Tijjaniyya Foundation of Nigeria and a former chairman of Fityanul Islam of Nigeria. 